{"title":"How to watch the Critérium du Dauphiné 2025","link":"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/how-to-watch-criterium-du-dauphine","date":1749139847000,"content":"<p><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a><br />\n<a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/how-to-watch-criterium-du-dauphine\">How to watch the Critérium du Dauphiné 2025</a></p>\n\n<p>The Tour’s biggest warm-up race, the Critérium du Dauphiné, kicks off this weekend in eastern France, with eight stages of racing scheduled between Sunday 8th to Sunday 15th June. </p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/criterium-du-dauphine-preview\">This year’s route</a> will cover some staple Tour climbs, including the <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/col-de-la-madeleine-cycling\">Col de la Madeleine</a>, <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/col-de-la-croix-de-fer-cycling\">Col de la Croix de Fer</a> and the Côte de Domancy, which will be used in the 2027 UCI Road World Championships.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>This year’s Dauphiné is set to be a thriller. Tadej Pogačar will make his long-awaited return to the race, ending a five-year hiatus from the Tour dress rehearsal. Alongside him, Jonas Vingegaard will be present, as will last year’s white jersey winner Remco Evenepoel. Joining them will be a blockbuster cast of Tour contenders, including Carlos Rodiguez, Enric Mas and Mattias Skjelmose.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You won’t want to miss this year’s edition. Who knows, it might even be more exciting than<a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/tour-de-france-route-live-tv-guide-startlist-stage-by-stage\"> the Tour de France.</a></p>\n\n\n\n\n\n<h2>Where and how to watch the 2025 Critérium du Dauphiné</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><div></div><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/06/20240609CDD0150-A.S.O.-Billy-Ceusters-970x647.webp\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/06/20240609CDD0150-A.S.O.-Billy-Ceusters-970x646.webp 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/06/20240609CDD0150-A.S.O.-Billy-Ceusters-300x200.webp 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/06/20240609CDD0150-A.S.O.-Billy-Ceusters-768x512.webp 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/06/20240609CDD0150-A.S.O.-Billy-Ceusters-1536x1024.webp 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/06/20240609CDD0150-A.S.O.-Billy-Ceusters-2048x1365.webp 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/06/20240609CDD0150-A.S.O.-Billy-Ceusters-750x500.webp 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/06/20240609CDD0150-A.S.O.-Billy-Ceusters-1140x760.webp 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/06/20240609CDD0150-A.S.O.-Billy-Ceusters-465x310.webp 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/06/20240609CDD0150-A.S.O.-Billy-Ceusters-620x413.webp 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/06/20240609CDD0150-A.S.O.-Billy-Ceusters-350x233.webp 350w\" /><figcaption>A.S.O./Billy Ceusters</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Critérium du Dauphiné will be shown live on TNT Sports 1 and 3 throughout the week in the UK and Ireland. To watch the race online, you can tune in via Discovery+ between 14:00 and 14:30 BST each day, except the penultimate stage, which starts at 13:30 BST.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Elsewhere, fans in the US can catch the action on Peacock and NBC Sports, in Canada it’ll be on FloBikes, in Australia it’s on SBS On Demand, and it’s on all the usual channels throughout Europe. <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/buying-guides/free-to-air-cycling\">If you’re looking for free-to-air coverage</a>, SBS is your best bet for English language commentary. For the most extensive broadcast, France 3’s coverage will be available to watch for free if you’re in France.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If the race isn’t being broadcast in your country or you are travelling abroad, a VPN will allow you to hide your device’s location to access content that is normally geo-blocked. One such VPN provider is <a href=\"https://go.expressvpn.com/m5yJGZ\" target=\"_blank\">ExpressVPN</a>, which is <a href=\"https://www.techradar.com/reviews/expressvpn\" target=\"_blank\">well reviewed</a>, helps users to find free-to-watch cycling, and costs start from around £5 per month.</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Read more: <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/how-to-watch-cycling-for-less-in-the-uk\">How to watch cycling for less in the UK</a></strong></li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Read more:</strong> <strong><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/buying-guides/free-to-air-cycling\">Which countries can watch cycling for free in 2025?</a></strong></li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/newsletters\"><img width=\"970\" height=\"332\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/Newsletter-flash-v2-1-970x332.webp\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/Newsletter-flash-v2-1-970x332.webp 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/Newsletter-flash-v2-1-300x103.webp 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/Newsletter-flash-v2-1-768x263.webp 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/Newsletter-flash-v2-1-1536x526.webp 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/Newsletter-flash-v2-1-2048x701.webp 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/Newsletter-flash-v2-1-750x257.webp 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/Newsletter-flash-v2-1-1140x390.webp 1140w\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2>Live TV