li><strong><strong>Discovery</strong>+:</strong> 14:25-16:25</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h4>Stage 3: Brioude – Charantonnay, Tuesday 10th June</h4>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>TNT Sports 3:</strong> 14:30-16:30</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong><strong>Discovery</strong>+: </strong>14:25-16:25</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h4>Stage 4: Charmes-sur-Rhône – Saint-Péray, Wednesday 11th June</h4>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>TNT Sports 1/3:</strong> 14:10-16:10</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong><strong>Discovery</strong>+:</strong> 14:25-16:25</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h4>Stage 5: Saint-Priest – Mâcon, Thursday 12th June</h4>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>TNT Sports 3:</strong> 14:30-16:30</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong><strong>Discovery</strong>+:</strong> 14:25-16:25</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h4>Stage 6: Valserhône – Combloux, Friday 13th June</h4>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>TNT Sports 1:</strong> 14:30-16:30</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong><strong>Discovery</strong>+: </strong>14:25-16:25</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h4>Stage 7: Grand-Aigueblanche – Valmeinier 1800, Saturday 14th June</h4>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>TNT Sports 3:</strong> 13:30-15:30</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong><strong>Discovery</strong>+: </strong>13:35-15:35</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h4>Stage 8: Val-d’Arc – Val-Cenis, Sunday 15th June</h4>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>TNT Sports 3:</strong> 14:15-16:30</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong><strong>Discovery</strong>+: </strong>14:15-16:25</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n<div>\r\n                <div>\r\n                   <div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <h4><span>Related Posts</span></h4>\r\n                      </div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <div>\r\n                            <div>\r\n                            <article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/cyclist-way-too-early-tour-de-france-2025-predictions\">Cyclist’s way too early Tour de France 2025 predictions</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n       